                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/834: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-19T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. Your 299 July 10, 7 p.m. has been copied to the American Group for comment.
                    You will be informed of its reply. For your confidential information you are
                    advised that the Department does not anticipate a favorable reply. Is the
                    Department to understand that proposal outlined in your 299, if adopted, takes
                    the place of postponement of indemnity payments proposed in your 280, June 23, 9
                        a.m.?<note n="37" xml:id="d568fn37">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_809">p. 809</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
